@startuml
title XML Display & Editing Application\nLayered Architecture — Component View

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam NoteBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7

skinparam package {
  BorderColor #444444
  FontStyle bold
  FontSize 13
}

skinparam component {
  BorderColor #444444
  BackgroundColor white
  FontSize 11
}

package "Layer 4: Presentation" #D6EAF8 {
  [XMLApplication]
  [XMLDisplay]
}

package "Layer 3: Application Logic" #D5F5E3 {
  [XMLLoader]
  [XMLEditor]
  [XMLValidator]
}

package "Layer 2: Domain" #FEF9E7 {
  [Domain Model\n(dom::Node, Document,\nElement, Attr, Text)] as Domain
}

package "Layer 1: Infrastructure" #FDEDEC {
  [XMLTokenizer]
  [XMLSerializer]
}

note right of [XMLApplication]
  **Constraint:** Only layer that
  interacts with the user (stdin/stdout).
  All mutations routed through Layer 3.
end note

note right of Domain
  **Constraint:** Upper layers depend only
  on the dom:: interfaces, not on the
  *_Impl classes. Interfaces form a
  stable Facade between layers.
end note

note right of [XMLTokenizer]
  **Constraint:** No dependency on
  any layer above.
end note

' Layer 4 → Layer 4 (peer)
[XMLApplication] --> [XMLDisplay] : renders /\nresolves index

' Layer 4 → Layer 3
[XMLApplication] --> [XMLLoader]  : load file
[XMLApplication] --> [XMLEditor]  : edit / save

' Layer 4 → Layer 2 (read-only)
[XMLDisplay] ..> Domain           : read-only traversal

' Layer 3 → Layer 3 (peer)
[XMLEditor]  --> [XMLValidator]   : validate before edit

' Layer 3 → Layer 2
[XMLLoader]  --> Domain           : build document tree
[XMLEditor]  --> Domain           : mutate document tree

' Layer 3 → Layer 1 (relaxed layering)
[XMLLoader]  --> [XMLTokenizer]   : tokenize input file
[XMLEditor]  --> [XMLSerializer]  : write output file

@enduml
